ReportText: EXAM: CHEST RADIOGRAPHY EXAM DATE: 04/26/2021 05:43 AM. CLINICAL HISTORY: Acute respiratory failure. COMPARISON: X-RAY CHEST 1 VIEW PORTABLE 04/25/2021 5:25 AM. TECHNIQUE: 1 view. FINDINGS: Lungs/Pleura: Right basilar airspace disease and left basilar airspace disease, similar to prior. No pneumothorax. Mediastinum: Within exam limitations, the cardiomediastinal contour is normal. Other: Endotracheal tube tip located 2.7 cm above the carina. Enteric tube courses below the diaphragm into the region of the stomach with tip off the confines of the film. Right upper extremity PICC tip located in the region of the junction of the SVC and right atrium. IMPRESSION: Right basilar airspace disease and left basilar airspace disease, similar to prior. Support hardware are located in standard positions, as described above.
